# Copy to `.env.local` and fill in. For production, set the same keys in Vercel:
# Project → Settings → Environment Variables (Production + Preview), then redeploy.

# Untitled UI PRO icons (`@untitledui-pro/icons`) — required for `npm install` / Vercel builds.
# Get your API key from Untitled UI → account / license. Set in Vercel for Production + Preview.
# Local: add to `.env.local` and run `export UNTITLEDUI_NPM_TOKEN=...` before `npm install`, or:
#   `export $(grep -v '^#' .env.local | xargs) && npm install`
# UNTITLEDUI_NPM_TOKEN=

# Supabase — required for auth and any client using getSupabaseBrowserClient().
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Canonical public origin for auth redirects (sign-up confirmation link, OAuth callback). No trailing slash.
# Production (Vercel): https://app.finsepa.com — ensures Supabase redirect_to is https + /auth/callback, not a bad browser origin.
# Local: omit to use http://localhost:3000 from the browser, or set NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ORIGIN=https://app.finsepa.com
#
# `npm run dev` / `dev:clean` / `dev:webpack` pin PORT=3000 and `-p 3000` so the app stays on http://localhost:3000.
# If something else is bound to 3000, run `npm run dev:free-port` (macOS/Linux) then `npm run dev` again.

# Supabase service role — server-only (watchlist counts, `/api/auth/signup-with-loops` admin generateLink). Never expose to the browser.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
#
# Supabase CLI (Cursor cannot run interactive `supabase login` — use a Personal Access Token instead):
# 1. https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens → Generate new token
# 2. Add to .env.local: SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=sbp_...
# 3. npm run supabase:login && npm run supabase:link
# SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# Sign-up abuse protection (bot floods hit `/api/auth/signup-with-loops` + direct Supabase Auth).
# EMERGENCY: set both in Vercel Production, redeploy, then run `npm run db:migrate` for billing-on-confirm trigger.
# AUTH_SIGNUP_DISABLED=1
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_SIGNUP_DISABLED=1
# Cloudflare Turnstile (free): https://dash.cloudflare.com → Turnstile → Finsepa widget → copy keys.
# Hostnames on the widget must include localhost + 127.0.0.1 for local dev (no :3000).
# Same TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY must be set in Supabase → Authentication → Bot and Abuse Protection.
# After editing .env.local, restart: npm run dev
# TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=
# Optional separate widget for localhost (Cloudflare hostnames: localhost, 127.0.0.1):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY_LOCAL=
# Also enable Turnstile under Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Bot and Abuse Protection (blocks direct signUp).
# AUTH_SIGNUP_LOOPS_API_ONLY=1
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_SIGNUP_LOOPS_API_ONLY=1
# Purge spam users after attack: node --env-file=.env.local scripts/purge-spam-auth-users.mjs [--delete]

# Auth emails (sign-up confirmation, password reset): use Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → SMTP
# with Loops as the provider (host smtp.loops.so, user "loops", password = Loops API key). See:
# https://loops.so/docs/smtp — credentials live in Supabase, not in these Next.js env vars.
# Enable "Confirm email" under Authentication → Providers → Email so sign-ups must verify.
#
# --- Inbox placement (if mail lands in spam) — mostly DNS + Loops, not app code ---
# 1. Loops → Settings → Domains: add a sending subdomain (recommended mail.finsepa.com), copy SPF/DKIM/MX/DMARC
#    into your DNS (Cloudflare: turn OFF proxy/orange cloud on DKIM CNAMEs), click Verify Records.
# 2. In every Loops transactional template: From = e.g. Finsepa <hello@mail.finsepa.com> (must match verified domain).
# 3. Supabase SMTP sender must use the same verified domain (not @gmail.com, not an unverified root domain).
# 4. Production: NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ORIGIN=https://app.finsepa.com so confirmation links are not localhost/http.
# 5. Test: https://www.mail-tester.com (aim for 9+/10) and Google Postmaster Tools for app.finsepa.com.
# 6. Warm up: new domains need consistent low volume before bulk; avoid spammy subject lines (ALL CAPS, “FREE!!!”).
# Docs: https://loops.so/docs/sending-domain https://loops.so/docs/deliverability/dmarc-dkim-setup
#
# If Supabase still returns "Error sending confirmation email" or email rate limits, Finsepa falls back to Loops HTTP API (needs service role + LOOPS_API_KEY):
# LOOPS_API_KEY=                    # required for fallback — from https://app.loops.so → Settings → API
# LOOPS_TRANSACTIONAL_ID_SIGNUP=  # optional; defaults to Finsepa sign-up template cm54x9u6103qnqa68w7cg1ls7
# LOOPS_TRANSACTIONAL_ID_PASSWORD_RESET=  # optional; defaults to password-reset template cmo1t3r8003870izrgv2vae6a
# LOOPS_TRANSACTIONAL_ID_PRO_ACTIVATED=   # optional; defaults to “Buy Pro Plan” template cmoo8ezzr0qrb0i2mhrw29zlx (Stripe invoice.paid subscription_create)
# LOOPS_TRANSACTIONAL_ID_PRO_RENEWED=     # optional; defaults to “Pro Plan Renew” template cmoo8r6n40k7y0izkctvh3nvq (Stripe invoice.paid subscription_cycle)
# LOOPS_TRANSACTIONAL_ID_WELCOME_TRIAL_START=cmpqlacpq1dux0j155z7t77cv  # “Welcome Trial Start” after Google sign-up or email confirm. Variables:
#   firstName, platformLink (button URL → https://app.finsepa.com/screener), trialDays (number), trialEndsAt, proInfoLine
#   Button href in Loops MUST be {data.platformLink} — not {{data.platformLink}} or {platformLink}
# LOOPS_TRANSACTIONAL_ID_TRIAL_ENDS_TOMORROW=cmreiej710iox0jywmmqplp54  # “Trial ends tomorrow”. Variables: firstName, trialEndsAt, billingLink ({data.billingLink} → /account?tab=billing)
# LOOPS_TRANSACTIONAL_ID_TRIAL_EXPIRED=cmreiek1w03lx0j3gmtbz8cps       # “Trial expired”. Variables: firstName, upgradeLink ({data.upgradeLink} → /activate-subscription)
# LOOPS_TRANSACTIONAL_ID_HELP_FEEDBACK=cmqjb6sdh11hr0j2pf1gcg0co  # Help modal → hi@finsepa.com. Publish template. From = hello@mail.finsepa.com. Reply-To = {data.userEmail} in Loops editor. LMX body uses {data.userName}, {data.userEmail}, {data.messageText}, {data.pageUrl}, {data.attachmentLinks} (single braces, not {{…}})
# LOOPS_TRANSACTIONAL_ID_GOOGLE_WELCOME=  # optional alias for WELCOME_TRIAL_START
# Create transactional templates with data variables: firstName, confirmationLink (sign-up + password reset)
# (confirmationLink = full Supabase verify URL). @see https://loops.so/docs/api-reference/send-transactional-email
# Supabase must allow your app callback in Authentication → URL Configuration → Redirect URLs, e.g.
# https://YOUR_DOMAIN/auth/callback?next=/screener (GET /api/auth/signup-with-loops reports loopsConfigured + adminConfigured)

# Logo.dev — required for correct stock/crypto logos via `/api/media/logo` (server never exposes token to browser).
# Get keys at https://www.logo.dev/
LOGO_DEV_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
# Optional: same publishable key, used only as fallback in server logo proxy
NEXT_PUBLIC_LOGO_DEV_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# Optional: cap Logo.dev upstream fetches per server instance (default 500000 / 30d)
# FINSEPA_LOGO_DEV_MAX_REQUESTS_PER_30D=500000

# SEC EDGAR — identify your app when fetching public Form 13F data (Superinvestors) and when resolving
# earnings “Slides / Filings” links (data.sec.gov submissions + filing indexes). Recommended in production.
# Example: Finsepa/1.0 (contact@yourdomain.com)
# @see https://www.sec.gov/os/accessing-edgar-data
SEC_EDGAR_USER_AGENT=

# Stripe billing (migration-safe setup)
# Primary account API key (used when STRIPE_ACCOUNTS_JSON is not provided)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
# Stripe webhook signing secret for /api/stripe/webhook?account=primary
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# Payment Links used by Upgrade modal checkout launcher (fallback when price IDs below are unset)
STRIPE_PAYMENT_LINK_MONTHLY=
STRIPE_PAYMENT_LINK_ANNUAL=
# Optional: Stripe Price IDs for Pro monthly / annual recurring prices. When both are set for the
# active account, checkout uses Stripe Checkout instead of Payment Links so the same `customer`
# is reused and Stripe does not create duplicate customers for one email on repeat purchases.
# STRIPE_PRICE_ID_MONTHLY=price_...
# STRIPE_PRICE_ID_ANNUAL=price_...
# Required for email login + in-app password change (server verifies bcrypt against auth.users).
# Local: copy Session pooler URI from Supabase Dashboard → Connect → Session pooler into .env.local
# Production (Vercel): set SUPABASE_POOLER_URL for Production + Preview, then redeploy.
# SUPABASE_POOLER_URL=postgresql://postgres.<ref>:<password>@aws-?.<region>.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
# If you use the Vercel Supabase integration, POSTGRES_URL / POSTGRES_HOST may be set automatically instead.
# Optional account key label (default: "primary")
# STRIPE_PRIMARY_ACCOUNT_KEY=primary
#
# Optional multi-account configuration (JSON array). Use this to run primary + legacy Stripe accounts safely.
# Example:
# STRIPE_ACCOUNTS_JSON=[{"key":"primary","secretKey":"sk_live_xxx","webhookSecret":"whsec_xxx","monthlyPaymentLink":"https://buy.stripe.com/..","annualPaymentLink":"https://buy.stripe.com/..","monthlyPriceId":"price_..","annualPriceId":"price_..","portalReturnUrl":"https://app.finsepa.com/account?tab=billing"},{"key":"legacy","secretKey":"sk_live_old","webhookSecret":"whsec_old","portalReturnUrl":"https://app.finsepa.com/account?tab=billing"}]
#
# Stripe CLI — already logged in on this machine (`stripe config --list`). Re-auth: npm run stripe:login
# Influencer promo codes (single-use, 1yr 100% off Pro): npm run stripe:influencer-codes
# Cursor Stripe MCP: .cursor/mcp.json → https://mcp.stripe.com (OAuth in Cursor Settings → MCP)

# SnapTrade — connect user brokerage accounts (read-only portal). Server-only keys; never expose to the browser.
# Sign up at https://snaptrade.com/ → Dashboard → API Keys (Client ID + Consumer Key).
# Requires `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` and migration `20260612120000_snaptrade_users.sql` (`npm run db:migrate`).
# SNAPTRADE_CLIENT_ID=
# SNAPTRADE_CONSUMER_KEY=

# Live 1D chart — EODHD WebSocket minute bars (Railway worker) + realtime OHLCV tail.
# Set on Vercel + locally for ops health: Railway service /health URL.
# FINSEPA_STOCK_MINUTE_BAR_READ=1 and FINSEPA_STOCK_MINUTE_BAR_WRITE=1 (default on)
# STOCK_MINUTE_INGEST_HEALTH_URL=https://your-railway-service.up.railway.app/health
# EODHD_API_KEY=

# Stock overview Key Indicators card (lazy + shared snapshot). Both flags required; restart dev server after change.
FINSEPA_KEY_INDICATORS=1
NEXT_PUBLIC_FINSEPA_KEY_INDICATORS=1

# Ops health dashboard — secret URL + password (no Finsepa login). Not indexed by search engines.
# Generate slug: openssl rand -base64 24 | tr '+/' '-_' | tr -d '='
# Visit https://app.finsepa.com/ops/YOUR_SLUG — wrong slug returns 404.
# ADMIN_HEALTH_SLUG=
# ADMIN_HEALTH_PASSWORD=
